</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1214,1599]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1538,1563]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Notes.</emphasis>
The species formerly was known from Nepal; hereby it is recorded for China for the first time. New data considerable extend the distribution pattern of 
<taxonomicName box="[727,861,1574,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Stenoloba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectilinea">
<emphasis box="[727,741,1575,1598]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[755,861,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">rectilinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
